  "playingCareerSummary": "One of the greatest leg-spinners in cricket history and an all-time great of the game: 145 Tests (708 wickets at 25.41), 194 ODIs. Played for Rajasthan Royals in the IPL (2008-2011), captaining the side that won the inaugural 2008 title.",
  "bio": "Rajasthan Royals' inaugural head coach and captain in 2008 — the original captain-coach who masterminded RR's inaugural IPL title with a squad built around young, unheralded Indian talent. Remained captain-coach through 2011, then continued as non-playing head coach for 2012 after retiring from active IPL cricket. His revolutionary tactical approach, embrace of data, and trust in youngsters defined the first chapter of Rajasthan Royals' identity. Replaced by Paddy Upton for IPL 2013.",
